		<div class="entry-content"><div class="w480"><figure class="media photo promo" itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope="" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/01/05/world/sub-russia-LN/sub-russia-blog480.jpg" itemtype="//schema.org/ImageObject" role="group"><span class="visually-hidden">Photo</span><div class="image"><img itemprop="url" itemid="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/01/05/world/sub-russia-LN/sub-russia-blog480.jpg" src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2014/01/05/world/sub-russia-LN/sub-russia-blog480.jpg" id="100000002650018" width="480" height="331" alt="President Vladimir V. Putin, right, took part in a friendly hockey match on Jan. 4 at the Bolshoy Ice Dome in Sochi. &lt;a href=&quot;//www.nytimes.com/2014/01/05/world/europe/putin-loosens-ban-on-protests-in-sochi.html&quot;&gt;Go to related articleÂ Â»&lt;/a&gt;"   /><meta itemprop="height" content="331"><meta itemprop="width" content="480"></div><figcaption class="caption" itemprop="description"><span class="caption-text">President Vladimir V. Putin, right, took part in a friendly hockey match on Jan. 4 at the Bolshoy Ice Dome in Sochi. <a href="//www.nytimes.com/2014/01/05/world/europe/putin-loosens-ban-on-protests-in-sochi.html">Go to related articleÂ Â»</a></span><span class="credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder"><span class="visually-hidden">Credit</span> Alexei Nikolsky/RIA Novosti Kremlin Press Service, via Associated Press</span></figcaption></figure></div>
<div class="w151 right module">
